<para>This class offers a bidirectional connection between <ref refid="structhise_1_1raw_1_1_data" kindref="compound">Data</ref> and its UI representation.</para><para>In order to use it, just add one of these as Member variable in your interface class:</para><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="keyword">class<sp/></highlight><highlight class="normal">MyInterface</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>MyInterface(<ref refid="classhise_1_1_main_controller" kindref="compound">hise::MainController</ref>*<sp/>mc):</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>s(</highlight><highlight class="stringliteral">&quot;My<sp/>Funky<sp/>Slider&quot;</highlight><highlight class="normal">),</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>connection(&amp;s,<sp/>mc,<sp/></highlight><highlight class="stringliteral">&quot;Sine<sp/>1&quot;</highlight><highlight class="normal">,<sp/>hise::SineSynth::SaturationAmount)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>addAndMakeVisible(s);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>s.setRange(0.0,<sp/>1.0,<sp/>0.01);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>}</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>juce::Slider<sp/>s;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>raw::UIConnection::Slider<sp/>connection;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">}</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> <verbatim>If you just want a more generic, but unidirectional connection (Processor-&gt;UI) take a look at the Reference class.</verbatim> </para>    </detaileddescription>
